Linear modeling of expression in IPF core samples

Hypothesis

Histopathological variables are related to differential expression. Build linear models to find these relationships. All analysis on this page is of log2-transformed RPKM data of IPF patients only.

Analysis

Examine distributions of vars

I log-transformed and z-scored all continuous phenotypic variables to prepare for linear modeling. Lets verify that the distributions now look normal.

Model expression by cell type

We have counts of six leukocyte types, lets model expression by the z-scores of those. Criteria: p < 0.05, absolute value of logFC > 0.5. Here log fold change is weird, its actually the log2 expression change per standard deviation unit of the histology variable.

Neutrophils, CD4 T cells, and eosinophils showed no differential expression.
